This paper deals with the formalization of default reasoning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses the semantics of first-order conditional logic, which is related to mathematical logic (cs.LO) and logic programming (cs.PL). The paper uses plausibility structures, which are a tool in machine learning and probabilistic reasoning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the lottery paradox, which is a topic in decision theory and game theory (cs.CC).
